ames[3] = 'ADDRESS'; ftypes[3] = 'address'; fnames[4] = 'PHONE'; ftypes[4] = 'phone'; }(jQuery)); var $mcj = jQuery.noConflict(true);</script><!--End mc_embed_signup--></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080550" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080550"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Do exercise bikes really help burn fat?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1689112608710" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1689112608710"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Cycling, both indoor and outdoor, is a great cardio option that can improve your general health, tone up your body, work out your lower body greatly, and improve your mental health as well.</p><p>This activity involves your aerobic and anaerobic capabilities which may result in great energy expenditure. You'll be able to burn a great amount of calories, however, consider the ratio between energy output and intake if your goal is to lose weight.</p><p>So, to be short - yes, a stationary bike to lose weight is helpful to put your body into a deficit of calories. Even a 30-minute ride each day could be enough to improve your physical condition and burn fat.</p><p>Aerobic, or cardio exercises are much more effective for burning calories than resistance training. Namely, this kind of workout is highly efficient in fighting excessive weight and facilitates lean mass. The <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20585293/" class="" target="_blank">research proved</a> this statement presenting the following data: young sedentary overweight women participated in this study, of around 22 years old with 25-29.9 BMI. They trained for 12 weeks of indoor cycling consisting of three sessions per week. The results of the study showed a reduction of 2.6% and 3.2% in body weight and of 4.3% and 5% in fat mass. Also, the lean mass increased by 2.3% and 2.6% respectively, and the heart rate in the rest decreased by 6.5% and 9% respectively after 24 and 36 sessions.</p><p>The amount of calories you can burn while training on the exercise bike depends on your body composition, weight, and fitness level. The intensity and duration of training also affect the weight loss process. For example, if you work out on a Rogue Echo air bike for 10 minutes, you’ll burn more calories than if you pedal on a stationary bike at a moderate pace.</p><p>Speaking about the number of calories you can burn, <a href="https://www.health.harvard.edu/diet-and-weight-loss/calories-burned-in-30-minutes-for-people-of-three-different-weights" class="" target="_blank">the statistics show the following</a>: approximately 200-400 calories in 30 minutes. An average user of 155 lb can burn 250 calories in a moderate cycling class for 30 minutes, and approximately 300 in a high-intensity ride.</p><p>What about the HIIT cycling workout, this type of training requires maximum effort and energy burst for short periods. Just 20 seconds of vigorous intensity and 10 seconds of rest, with eight cycles, will help you to burn a sufficient amount of calories. Additionally, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6722762/" class="" target="_blank">research indicated </a>that a 12-week indoor cycling experiment reduced body mass by 3.1% (2.2 kg), with a combination of other activities, i.e., walking.</p><p>Exercising on a stationary bike is useful to <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20585735/" class="" target="_blank">manage serum lipid levels in overweight</a> people along with consistent training regime and proper nutrition.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1692129522935" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1692129522935" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/4f5a6cf8-f9e8-4322-a0b5-e5ab1cbeab93/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-air-bike-training.jpg" alt="athlete air bike training" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athlete air bike training" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1695734498841" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1695734498841"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What to look for in the best exercise bike for weight loss?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691605560830" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1691605560830"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>A multifunctional and highly adjustable exercise bike is the right choice for users aiming to lose weight and burn more calories. In this section, we'll describe the key features that the best stationary bike for weight loss should have to provide a rider with more challenging yet comfortable training.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1689112597263" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1689112597263" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Adjustability</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1695734510327" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1695734510327"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The adjustability option is vital to vouch for a comfortable position on the bike which can directly influence the quality and duration of your training. You are best to choose an exercise bike with an adjustable seat and handlebars. What's more, the more settings it has, the better you'll manage to accommodate the bike to your body composition and position preferences. So, a 4-way adjustable seat and handles are the best variant for maximizing your comfort while training.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691605572638" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1691605572638" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Resistance/Incline&nbsp;</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691605583844" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1691605583844"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The feature of changing the resistance and incline settings is obviously the most important in helping you burn more calories. These two options relate to the intensity of your training and influence the endeavors you'll put in during the ride.</p><p>The resistance option is a perfect way to check your physical condition and make your legs stronger. While the incline option can imitate riding uphills, or cross-country terrains with hilly ground. So, altogether these options will make you push harder and increase your functional threshold of power.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1692169016634" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1692169016634" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1692169016621" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1692169016621" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1692169016658" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1692169016658"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1692169016607" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1692169016607" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="512" height="512" data-width="50%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="512" natural-height="512"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1692169016657" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1692169016657"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="">Consider the type of resistance system when choosing a stationary bike (magnetic or fan) for workout intensity. Opt for comfortable features like wide seats with gel padding and handles covered in foam or rubber. If you prefer ease of assembly, look for bikes with clear instructions or consider professional delivery and assembly services.</div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1692169016618" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1692169016618" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564763470" data-id="1686564763470"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1692169016609" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1692169016609" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" target="_blank"><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/fc0a1a19-2e31-4fa8-a43b-9c408a123923/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Oleksiy.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="531" height="533" data-width="20%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="531" natural-height="533"></a></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564765807" data-id="1686564765807"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1692169016605" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1692169016605"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" class="" target="_blank">Oleksiy Torokhtiy</a></b></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1692169016590" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1692169016590"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700;">Olympic Weightlifting&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 700; color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Champion</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691605596536" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1691605596536" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Applied mechanism</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691605608299" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1691605608299"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Try to choose exercise bikes with belt-drive mechanisms over models with chain-drive systems. First, such bikes are of a higher quality, the operating mechanism is more durable and long-lasting. Second, they are quieter while at work and don't disturb you. The belt mechanism provides a very smooth and almost noise-free ride, so you can concentrate on your training goals.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691605641793" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1691605641793" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. Comfort</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691605649128" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1691605649128"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>How does comfort relate to the choice of an exercise bike to lose belly fat and burn calories? An ergonomic seat, reliable backrest (recumbent bikes), sufficient number of options to adjust the bike to your body composition, availability of dual-sided pedals, and so on creates as perfect as possible opportunities to concentrate on your performance and gain the desired results. So, you don't need to be distracted from training to change the seat or handlebars position.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691605658873" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1691605658873" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">5. Availability of built-in programs and workouts</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691605672878" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1691605672878"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The more tech-savvy your exercise bike is, the greater opportunities you'll get to diversify your training, and consequently pump up your body. If your goal is to burn more calories, then consider bikes with monitors that enable you to track your performance, namely see your speed, resistance level, pulse zones, and calories burned.</p><p>Also, mind models that are compatible with fitness applications and can be connected via Bluetooth or ANT+ to heart rate monitors, fitness watches, etc. in order to get more detailed information about your workout progress. Such stationary bikes are more expensive, but it's a worthy investment.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1659008080577" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1659008080577" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1658828961229" data-id="1658828961229"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1690538490105" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1690538490105" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/1c289534-4548-4d31-ae60-f8e7467fe29c/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/man-air-bike-workout.jpg" alt="man air bike workout" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="man air bike workout" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1690521958192" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1690521958192"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">How to speed up weight loss on an exercise bike?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1690522042710" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1690522042710"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>If you're curious about how to get more incredible results in losing weight while exercising on the stationary bike, we'll tell you what things you should follow to succeed in burning more calories. The following points will help you to optimize your exercise bike for weight loss to get a lean body:</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1695734606804" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1695734606804" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Be consistent</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1695734616726" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1695734616726"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>To get incredible results you need to be persistent and consistent in your training routine. By following regular workouts, you'll be able to improve your performance, and physical condition, and will increase your energy output after each training session. You should outline what type of training is comfortable for you and which workout assists you in showing good performance metrics.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1695734621195" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1695734621195" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Switching the resistance levels</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1695734624697" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1695734624697"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Always change the resistance level throughout the training to pump up your heart rate and make yourself sweat more. Start pedaling at low levels to warm up properly, then increase the resistance gradually depending on your training plan. If you're full of energy, go up by imitating riding up the hills and hit the next pulse zone.</p><p>The majority of the observed indoor bikes for weight loss are equipped with 22 to 26 resistance levels, while Peloton comes with 100 magnetic resistance levels. Such a wide range of tension enables a rider to adjust the intensity to suit their fitness level and goals.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1695734621092" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1695734621092" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Add HIIT training</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1695734622568" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1695734622568"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Have you ever tried to add some HIIT to your rides on the indoor bike? If not, don't miss this chance to burn an incredible amount of calories in one training session. This is an effective calorie-burning exercise that activates your anaerobic capabilities.</p><p>As it's super intensive training, your body's oxygen supply isn't enough, so it turns to another energy source - your fat deposits. HIIT training could be sprinting for 30 seconds with 30 seconds of rest. Also, for the next set, you can increase the resistance level and up your pace. This way you'll burn more calories in a shorter time.</p><p>HIIT cycling is effective in raising your metabolism. Meaning, your body will be able to continue burning calories even after the workout. A recent <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7908148/" class="" target="_blank">study showed</a> that providing different workout structures, i.e., mixed pyramid, ascending interval, and descending interval bouts, should be varied to achieve high energy expenditure.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080601" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080601"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQ</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080602" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080602"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Can you lose weight by riding a stationary bike?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080603" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080603"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Yes, you can lose weight by regular training on a stationary bike. For instance, a 155-lb rider can burn around 252 calories in 30 minutes of moderate cycling by getting a calorie deficit that allows them to lose weight respectively.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080605" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080605"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Will riding a stationary bike 30 minutes a day help lose weight?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1659008080604" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1659008080604"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Yes, a 30-minute ride on a stationary bike will help to burn fat and lose weight. Considering the Harvard reports, a 125-lb person will burn around 210 calories at a moderate pace, while a high-intensity ride can help to burn 320 calories. The more you weigh, the more calories you'll burn.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1692123223744" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1692123223744"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">How much cycling to lose 1kg in a week?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1692123233853" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1692123233853"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">To lose 1 kg of weight you need to <a href="https://conditionandnutrition.com/how-much-cycling-to-lose-1kg-including-all-weight-groups/" class="" target="_blank">burn around 8000 calories</a>. One hour of steady indoor cycling can burn 300-400 calories, consequently two hours - 600-700 calories depending on your weight.  So, overall, you need 10 hours of cycling to lose 1 kg, or five cycling workouts for two hours in a week.</p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1685568799611" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1685568799611" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="modul